Personal Finance Tracker
Description
The Personal Finance Tracker is a Python-based application designed to help you keep track of your financial transactions. The tracker allows users to record and categorize their transactions, analyze totals within specified date ranges or other criteria, and visualize this data using graphs. It's a straightforward and customizable tool for managing your finances.

Features
Transaction Logging: Easily log financial transactions with date, category, and description.
Data Analysis: Tally totals within specific date ranges or by categories.
Visualization: Project your financial data on a graph for better insights.
Requirements
Python 3.x
pandas library
matplotlib library
You can install the required libraries using pip:

bash
Copy code
pip install pandas matplotlib
How to Use
Clone the Repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone git@github.com:MelissaPennington/Personal-Finance-Tracker.git
Navigate to the Project Directory:

bash
Copy code
cd Personal-Finance-Tracker
Run the Program:

bash
Copy code
python3 main.py
This will initialize the CSV file if it doesn't exist and allow you to start logging your transactions.

Track Your Finances:

Add transactions to the CSV file or through the program interface (when implemented).
Use the analysis features to tally totals by date range, category, or other criteria.
Visualize your financial data using graphs.
